tempest/lib/auth.py.message:
Good question. Here are the docs we have in keystone for system-scope authentication [0].

Keystone considers the following authentication payload valid for getting system-scoped tokens:

  "scope": {
    "system": {
      "all": true
     }
  }

This is because we wanted to leave the implementation open to allow scoping to service catalog entries in the future. For example:

  "scope": {
    "system": {
      "service": $SERVICE_ID
    }
  }

Which would result in a token scoped to a specific service. This hasn't been implemented yet, but hopefully helps explain why we consider "all: True" to be special since we intend it to represent all services in the deployment.


[0] https://developer.openstack.org/api-ref/identity/v3/index.html?expanded=token-authentication-with-scoped-authorization-detail#id30

